b'' b'' b" let's say i have two rectangles on the canvas(see above)" b' one intersecting the other...' b' now, i would like to delete one of the rectangles.' b' the way i do it is to create another gc wherein i use the' b' gxxor logical function and simply redraw the rectangle using the' b'newly' b' created graphics context thus deleting it for all apparent purposes.' b' a problem with this approach is that at the points of intersection' b'the pixel' b' locations belonging to the other rectangle also become white, which' b'is' b' something that should be avoided.' b'' b'you could set up a bitmap with a mask in it. clear the' b'bitmap, draw the rectangle to be deleted with gxor. draw the one' b'that is to stay with gxclear. then gxxor the entire pixmap with' b'the screen.' b'' b'note that this is a pretty effective way of animation, if you ever' b'need to do that (replace the gxclear with a gxxor).' b'' b'----------' b'joe hildebrand' b'software engineer' b'fuentez systems concepts' b'(703)273-1447' b'' b'standard disclaimers apply' 